cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI

The paper describes a novel neural network architecture for predicting ventricular tachyarrhythmias using patient metadata and multi-task networks. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The focus on neural networks and machine learning techniques makes cs.LG the most likely category, followed by cs.CE and cs.NE. The use of features based on heart rate variability and frequency analysis suggests a potential fit with cs.CV, while the focus on patient metadata and multi-task objectives aligns with cs.AI.
